maybe we should get you to a hospital.

486
00:37:41.600 --> 00:37:43.600
No, you could've... Excuse me.

487
00:37:43.640 --> 00:37:48.480
Hey, could you hold still right there?

488
00:37:49.360 --> 00:37:54.880
Oh, yeah. I'm starting
to feel a little better.

489
00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:59.560
Ben! Oh, my God. You're fine.

490
00:38:03.480 --> 00:38:07.520
OK. Come on, Rocky. Get up.

491
00:38:08.160 --> 00:38:11.000
Ouch! Yeah.

492
00:38:11.680 --> 00:38:16.600
Don't feel bad. If I had a nickel for every
fist fight I got into during a chick flick...

493
00:38:16.640 --> 00:38:18.360
It wasn't that bad.

494
00:38:18.400 --> 00:38:24.440
Getting punched in the face sucked, but
getting cared for afterwards was nice.

495
00:38:24.480 --> 00:38:27.800
Oh, yeah.
Florence Nightingale syndrome.

496
00:38:27.840 --> 00:38:31.680
- Shall I tape the game for you tonight?
- No need.

497
00:38:31.720 --> 00:38:35.880
I'll be watching the Knicks
from the comfort of my own home.

498
00:38:35.920 --> 00:38:37.480
How'd you swing that?

499
00:38:37.520 --> 00:38:41.200
- The coup de grâce. Heavyweight.
- You're making the lamb.

500
00:38:41.240 --> 00:38:46.880
- A woman loves a man who can cook.
- Bringing out the big guns.

501
00:38:46.920 --> 00:38:51.760
- They forgot my bacon again.
- I can't believe you got him knocked out.

502
00:38:51.800 --> 00:38:53.680
Only for a few seconds.

503
00:38:53.720 --> 00:38:59.120
He was the most adorable
unconscious man ever.

504
00:38:59.160 --> 00:39:03.960
Are you dating him
or are you contemplating adoption?

505
00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:09.320
Andie, I am loving
your notes on this piece.

506
00:39:09.880 --> 00:39:12.240
- Thanks.
- When do you see him again?

507
00:39:12.280 --> 00:39:16.480
Tonight. He's invited me over for dinner.

508
00:39:16.520 --> 00:39:20.080
Marvellous.
I've got a feeling about this one.

509
00:39:20.120 --> 00:39:22.520
Thanks, Lana.

510
00:39:22.560 --> 00:39:25.280
I hate it when she
pops her head in like that.

511
00:39:25.320 --> 00:39:31.280
I heard that.
And Andie, tonight, take smaller bites.

512
00:39:32.440 --> 00:39:34.600
Oh, my God!

513
00:39:34.640 --> 00:39:39.560
Disgusting. I can barely eat over here.

514
00:39:41.960 --> 00:39:46.080
Come on in, the door's open.

515
00:39:46.520 --> 00:39:48.560
- Hi.
- Hey, there.

516
00:39:48.600 --> 00:39:55.560
I hope you brought your appetite, girl.
We've got a feast tonight.

517
00:39:58.520 --> 00:40:01.920
Benny, isn't that sweet?

518
00:40:01.960 --> 00:40:04.040
Pour yourself a glass of wine.

519
00:40:04.080 --> 00:40:07.840
We got dinner in about five,
tip-off in about eight.

520
00:40:07.880 --> 00:40:11.400
Great, I'm starving.

521
00:40:21.680 --> 00:40:25.320
Oh, so perfectly pink!

522
00:40:37.760 --> 00:40:42.240
<i>Pour la piece de résistance.</i>

523
00:40:46.000 --> 00:40:50.560
Sheryl, Tori,
Sinéad, Jewel, Fiona, Carly...

524
00:40:50.600 --> 00:40:53.160
...the gang's all here!

525
00:40:53.200 --> 00:40:55.640
Great.

526
00:40:56.000 --> 00:40:58.320
Got two minutes to game time.

527
00:40:58.360 --> 00:41:04.760
<i>You walked into the party
like you were walking onto a yacht</i>

528
00:41:04.800 --> 00:41:10.240
<i>Your hat strategically dipped
below one eye</i>

529
00:41:10.280 --> 00:41:13.400
<i>Your scarf it was apricot</i>

530
00:41:13.440 --> 00:41:15.960
Wow, look at all this stuff.

531
00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:19.640
- You had one eye in the mirror
- Cute.

532
00:41:19.680 --> 00:41:22.440
Saw the new comforter.

533
00:41:22.480 --> 00:41:28.640
<i>And all the girls dreamed that they'd be
Ben's partner, they'd be Ben's partner</i>

534
00:41:28.680 --> 00:41:31.360
- You're so vain
- What's in the box?

535
00:41:31.400 --> 00:41:33.760
Oh...

536
00:41:35.360 --> 00:41:38.160
- It's a baby fern.
- Really?

537
00:41:38.200 --> 00:41:46.280
It's like our relationship. A helpless
little baby in need of tender loving care.

538
00:41:46.720 --> 00:41:49.520
- Thank you.
- You had me several years ago

539
00:41:49.560 --> 00:41:52.040
Sit down.

540
00:41:52.080 --> 00:41:55.800
Have a seat. Get ready.

541
00:41:56.440 --> 00:42:00.240
Game two.
Welcome to the front row, madam.

542
00:42:00.280 --> 00:42:03.200
Oh, up here!

543
00:42:05.480 --> 00:42:11.040
Dinner is served. Chef's special tonight,
lamb with a cherry glaze.

544
00:42:11.080 --> 00:42:17.000
Start you off with the main dish,
right about there.

545
00:42:17.280 --> 00:42:20.480
A few carrots...

546
00:42:20.680 --> 00:42:24.240
Whoa. Hey, hey. You OK?

547
00:42:24.280 --> 00:42:27.400
It's beautiful.

548
00:42:28.280 --> 00:42:30.200
- Thanks.
- You're beautiful.

549
00:42:30.240 --> 00:42:34.360
The game, the whole thing...

550
00:42:34.480 --> 00:42:37.840
I wish I ate meat.

551
00:42:40.480 --> 00:42:45.720
<i>Mary had a little lamb, little lamb...</i>

552
00:42:46.280 --> 00:42:50.240
Take it away before I gag.

553
00:42:50.360 --> 00:42:54.000
This stuff's for cows.

554
00:42:59.640 --> 00:43:01.840
- Hi.
- How are you doing?

555
00:43:01.880 --> 00:43:06.640
- It's just a little indigestion.
- Are you OK?

556
00:43:06.680 --> 00:43:10.480
Excuse me. Do you know
the score of the Knicks game?

557
00:43:10.520 --> 00:43:13.880
Do I look like
the kind of person who would?

558
00:43:13.920 --> 00:43:16.960
No, you don't.

559
00:43:18.840 --> 00:43:21.280
Is something wrong with the barley?

560
00:43:21.320 --> 00:43:24.000
No, no...

561
00:43:28.440 --> 00:43:32.560
My boyfriend thinks I'm fat!

562
00:43:34.000 --> 00:43:38.240
And I can't eat in front of him.
I can't eat in front of you!

563
00:43:38.280 --> 00:43:44.560
- I have to go to the bathroom.
- I don't think you're...

564
00:43:44.960 --> 00:43:48.760
I don't think she's fat.

565
00:43:56.040 --> 00:43:57.480
What's happening?

566
00:43:57.520 --> 00:44:01.000
Spree just tied it up.
23 seconds left, Knicks ball.

567
00:44:01.040 --> 00:44:03.480
Oh, come on!

568
00:44:03.520 --> 00:44:05.120
There it is.

569
00:44:05.160 --> 00:44:09.720
That was in! Come on, get it back.

570
00:44:11.280 --> 00:44:14.640
Get the ball back!

571
00:44:15.880 --> 00:44:18.120
- Get back!
- No! Damn!

572
00:44:18.160 --> 00:44:23.920
<i>And the game has run out. The Kings
have their first win of the series.</i>

573
00:44:23.960 --> 00:44:26.720
Next game.

574
00:44:32.240 --> 00:44:35.645
Well, that was fun.

575
00:44:35.680 --> 00:44:40.680
Eleven twenty-five sports. There we are.

576
00:44:44.600 --> 00:44:47.320
- Sorry we missed the game.
- Pose, pose.

577
00:44:47.360 --> 00:44:51.160
Come back. Reverse!
There we go, baby.

578
00:44:51.200 --> 00:44:57.360
- Can't believe he missed that shot.
- Take it! Take it!

579
00:44:57.400 --> 00:45:01.560
How'd you know he was going to miss it?

580
00:45:01.600 --> 00:45:07.360
He always misses
the shot from the top of the key.

581
00:45:13.160 --> 00:45:18.520
Houston never misses
from the top of the key.

582
00:45:27.120 --> 00:45:30.760
Does Princess Sophia
want to come out and play?

583
00:45:30.800 --> 00:45:33.560
Who's she?

584
00:45:35.840 --> 00:45:39.560
No, no, no. Whoa, whoa.

585
00:45:39.960 --> 00:45:41.880
You're kidding me, right?

586
00:45:41.920 --> 00:45:46.080
Little? Big? I don't know, we will find out!

587
00:45:46.120 --> 00:45:49.840
Hang on, there. Oh, no.

588
00:45:50.600 --> 00:45:54.680
Listen, you can't name
my member Princess Sophia.

589
00:45:54.720 --> 00:45:59.560
- Yes, I can.
- If you're gonna name my member,

590
00:45:59.600 --> 00:46:05.840
it's got to be something masculine like
Spike, Butch or Krull the Warrior King.

591
00:46:05.880 --> 00:46:08.640
What did you just say?

592
00:46:08.680 --> 00:46:10.840
Spike. You know what I mean?

593
00:46:10.880 --> 00:46:13.680
- No, after Spike.
- Butch.

594
00:46:13.720 --> 00:46:16.640
After Butch.

595
00:46:18.240 --> 00:46:20.320
Krull the Warrior King.

596
00:46:20.360 --> 00:46:26.400
Does Krull the Warrior King
want to come out and play?

597
00:46:27.440 --> 00:46:29.560
- Oh, come on.
- No.

598
00:46:29.600 --> 00:46:34.440
- Krully-Wully! Krull!
- You know what?

599
00:46:34.480 --> 00:46:36.960
Due to intense humiliation,

600
00:46:37.000 --> 00:46:42.440
the King has momentarily
abdicated his throne.

601
00:46:44.800 --> 00:46:47.160
In that case...

602
00:46:47.200 --> 00:46:51.000
...I'd better get going.

603
00:46:52.920 --> 00:46:57.480
Take care of our love fern, honey.

604
00:47:12.240 --> 00:47:14.480
Hi.

605
00:47:14.760 --> 00:47:18.120
- Can I see you tomorrow?
- Really?

606
00:47:18.160 --> 00:47:20.920
I hope so.

607
00:47:21.480 --> 00:47:24.480
- Call me. And I'll call you.
- Sweet dreams.

608
00:47:24.520 --> 00:47:26.600
Answer your phone.

609
00:47:26.640 --> 00:47:29.000
What?

610
00:47:30.640 --> 00:47:34.360
- What was icy again?
- Arctic, freezing, frigid.

611
00:47:34.400 --> 00:47:36.960
- And glitter?
- Thayer's favourite movie.

612
00:47:37.000 --> 00:47:39.040
It was underrated.

613
00:47:39.080 --> 00:47:42.160
Glint, glisten, scintillation.

614
00:47:42.200 --> 00:47:45.120
- Scintillation's not bad.
- It sucks.

615
00:47:45.160 --> 00:47:49.040
Guys, let's take a break.
A little coffee, nine-ball.

616
00:47:49.080 --> 00:47:53.600
Maybe I'll be able to concentrate,
as the woman is driving me crazy.

617
00:47:53.640 --> 00:47:57.760
Which one, Andie or Princess Sophia?

618
00:47:57.800 --> 00:47:59.240
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

619
00:47:59.280 --> 00:48:01.880
After the game,
you called her a goddess.

620
00:48:01.920 --> 00:48:07.480
Oh, she was. That was the good Andie,
this amazing, fun, cool, sexy woman.

621
00:48:07.520 --> 00:48:12.560
I'm talking about the evil Andie. It's like
a crack-enhanced Kathie Lee Gifford.

622
00:48:12.600 --> 00:48:16.800
- She's probably bipolar.
- Her south pole's definitely prevailing.

623
00:48:16.840 --> 00:48:20.400
All you got to do
is rock her for five more days.

624
00:48:20.440 --> 00:48:22.880
- Muffin!
- Shouldn't be too hard.

625
00:48:22.920 --> 00:48:24.360
- Hi!
- Andie!

626
00:48:24.400 --> 00:48:28.040
Sweetie, we were just talking about you!
Hello, there.

627
00:48:28.080 --> 00:48:30.320
- You look gorgeous.
- Thank you.

628
00:48:30.360 --> 00:48:35.040
- This is Tony and this is Thayer.
- Benny-Wenny's told me all about you.

629
00:48:35.080 --> 00:48:38.680
Well, Benny-Wenny's
said wonderful things about you.

630
00:48:38.720 --> 00:48:41.600
They don't look so simple-minded.

631
00:48:41.640 --> 00:48:45.680
Honey, look what I got for us.

632
00:48:45.720 --> 00:48:49.360
Look at that! Come on.

633
00:48:49.440 --> 00:48:52.480
- Wow.
- Look at him go. What is it?

634
00:48:52.520 --> 00:48:57.640
- It's a Chinese Crested, of course.
- No kidding, a Chinese Crested.

635
00:48:57.680 --> 00:49:00.240
So, it's like a dog, right?

636
00:49:00.280 --> 00:49:04.720
- Whoa! There he is!
- Ben, you're hurting Krull's feelings.

637
00:49:04.760 --> 00:49:07.880
- Krull, is it?
- Krull the Warrior King.

638
00:49:07.920 --> 00:49:12.080
- Sure, that's clearly what...
- Wait, there's more.

639
00:49:12.120 --> 00:49:15.440
What's that?
For me? Get out of town.

640
00:49:15.480 --> 00:49:18.360
- Try it on.
- It's like the inside of a raincoat.

641
00:49:18.400 --> 00:49:21.400
- Matching!
- That's going to fit nicely.

642
00:49:21.440 --> 00:49:23.120
No, Ben, put it on.

643
00:49:23.160 --> 00:49:25.720
You should. In case it doesn't fit.

644
00:49:25.760 --> 00:49:33.000
- Manners never hurt anybody.
- I was saving it for a special occasion.

645
00:49:33.040 --> 00:49:35.760
Oh, yeah, it's nice. Huh?

646
00:49:35.800 --> 00:49:39.120
You're a vision in khaki.

647
00:49:39.160 --> 00:49:42.080
It's gonna be a happy family.

648
00:49:42.120 --> 00:49:45.720
- Just the three of us.
- We are, aren't we?

649
00:49:45.760 --> 00:49:49.080
- Wow.
- He's our boy, Ben.

650
00:49:49.120 --> 00:49:52.480
See, that's sweet.

651
00:49:55.320 --> 00:50:01.360
Hey, Andie, it's good to see you too,
sweetie. Gotcha!

652
00:50:01.600 --> 00:50:04.800
He's not potty-trained yet.

653
00:50:04.840 --> 00:50:09.840
- Oh, wow. He's a pisser!
- Oh, God. No!

654
00:50:10.200 --> 00:50:12.880
Come here, tinkle king.

655
00:50:12.920 --> 00:50:14.640
You tinkle-tinkles.

656
00:50:14.680 --> 00:50:18.200
Well, congratulations, little plaid family.

657
00:50:18.240 --> 00:50:22.360
We've got work to do, but we're on
for poker at your house this week, huh?

658
00:50:22.400 --> 00:50:24.320
Boys' night!

659
00:50:24.360 --> 00:50:26.920
It was nice meeting you and Krull.

660
00:50:26.960 --> 00:50:28.600
Bye. Say bye, Krully.

661
00:50:28.640 --> 00:50:31.480
A little soap and water'll fix it.

662
00:50:31.520 --> 00:50:34.280
Come here.

663
00:50:34.560 --> 00:50:37.880
- Do you love him?
- Oh, I do.

664
00:50:37.920 --> 00:50:42.080
Look at Krull's necklace. It's got
more ice than Liberace, don't you?

665
00:50:42.120 --> 00:50:46.240
It's just a little frosting.

666
00:50:47.320 --> 00:50:50.920
- Frosting?
- Frosting.

667
00:50:50.960 --> 00:50:53.520
We were thinking bold, new, fresh.

668
00:50:53.560 --> 00:50:57.800
- Frost yourself.
- Excuse me?

669
00:50:58.240 --> 00:51:00.040
The slogan for the campaign.

670
00:51:00.080 --> 00:51:02.440
- You frost a cake.
- I'm talking diamonds.

671
00:51:02.480 --> 00:51:07.080
They're frosting. As in, Whoa,
would you check out her frosting?

672
00:51:07.120 --> 00:51:09.840
Frost yourself.
How did you come up with it?

673
00:51:09.880 --> 00:51:12.920
From the woman who's fallen for me.

674
00:51:12.960 --> 00:51:16.640
It may work,
but as for her falling in love with you,

675
00:51:16.680 --> 00:51:20.120
- I'll decide that at the party.
- If you get her there.

676
00:51:20.160 --> 00:51:23.400
Just think about it,
Ladies, frost yourself.

677
00:51:23.440 --> 00:51:25.120
Frost yourself.

678
00:51:25.160 --> 00:51:29.040
- Introduce it at the party.
- It'll be the theme! Everything frosted.

679
00:51:29.080 --> 00:51:31.000
- Martini glasses.
- Chandeliers.

680
00:51:31.040 --> 00:51:33.240
- Jewels everywhere.
- The women.

681
00:51:33.280 --> 00:51:39.000
- The whole party a sparkling diamond.
- All of it frosted.

682
00:51:39.035 --> 00:51:44.720
- Women of New York, frost yourselves!
- Hey, frost this!

683
00:51:44.760 --> 00:51:47.960
Well, I like it.

684
00:51:50.840 --> 00:51:53.920
Yeah, yeah. I hear you.

685
00:51:53.960 --> 00:51:56.880
<i>You have 17 new messages.</i>

686
00:51:56.920 --> 00:52:00.040
<i>Message 1 received at 5.44.</i>

687
00:52:00.080 --> 00:52:04.120
- Hi, sweetie-pea. Where are you?
- I'm not home.

688
00:52:04.160 --> 00:52:08.840
- Message 2, 5.47.
- It's Andie. Guess you're not home.

689
00:52:08.880 --> 00:52:14.760
- Message 3, received 5.48.
- Are you not answering your phone?

690
00:52:14.800 --> 00:52:18.720
- Message 4, received 5.49.
- Hey, buddy. Game 3 tonight.

691
00:52:18.760 --> 00:52:20.520
<i>Blondie's, don't be late.</i>

692
00:52:20.560 --> 00:52:24.280
- Who is it?
- It's me.

693
00:52:24.600 --> 00:52:27.560
<i>It's me!</i>

694
00:52:29.400 --> 00:52:31.200
- Ow!
- What a surprise!

695
00:52:31.240 --> 00:52:33.760
- I tried to get hold of you.
- Yeah?

696
00:52:33.800 --> 00:52:37.560
- I did something kind of wacky.
- Yeah?

697
00:52:37.600 --> 00:52:43.400
I composited our faces together
to see what our kids would look like.

698
00:52:43.440 --> 00:52:46.720
Our Family Album!

699
00:52:57.880 --> 00:53:00.720
You don't want to see our children?

700
00:53:00.760 --> 00:53:04.720
We don't have... children.

701
00:53:19.560 --> 00:53:23.560
You know what?
I'm sorry, I didn't mean it like that.

702
00:53:23.600 --> 00:53:26.680
Show me, show me. Please, show me.

703
00:53:26.720 --> 00:53:31.840
- We don't have children!
- I thought you meant Krull. I just...

704
00:53:31.880 --> 00:53:34.400
- Can I see them?
- You don't want to.

705
00:53:34.440 --> 00:53:39.560
I do. Please, please show 'em to me.
I really do want to see 'em.

706
00:53:39.600 --> 00:53:42.000
Really?

707
00:53:42.040 --> 00:53:44.640
- Yeah.
- OK.

708
00:53:44.680 --> 00:53:48.120
That's our wedding.

709
00:53:49.200 --> 00:53:53.880
And this is our first child, Benny Junior.

710
00:53:53.920 --> 00:53:56.280
Yeah.

711
00:53:56.840 --> 00:53:59.920
There's us vacationing in Hawaii.

712
00:53:59.960 --> 00:54:06.000
Little Andie's on my shoulders and...
Benjamin Junior on yours.

713
