01:32:37.800 --> 01:32:43.640
Come on, Ben.
Ladies and gentlemen, Benjamin Barry!

1191
01:32:44.360 --> 01:32:47.320
Come on, Ben.

1192
01:32:53.680 --> 01:32:56.520
Thank you. Andie! Whoa, don't run off!

1193
01:32:56.560 --> 01:33:00.280
You do not want this young lady
to leave the room.

1194
01:33:00.320 --> 01:33:03.160
Thayer, Tony,
would you stop her, please?

1195
01:33:03.200 --> 01:33:09.360
You see, tonight, the really special event
is that we will be singing a duet.

1196
01:33:09.400 --> 01:33:15.920
Yes, Miss Andie Anderson.
Give her a warm round of applause.

1197
01:33:19.400 --> 01:33:21.000
Knock 'em out.

1198
01:33:21.040 --> 01:33:26.520
What will our song be?
Maybe one of her personal favourites.

1199
01:33:26.560 --> 01:33:30.080
Marvin, do you know You're So Vain?

1200
01:33:30.120 --> 01:33:36.560
- That's not one of my songs.
- Can you work with me? Yeah?

1201
01:33:40.680 --> 01:33:46.280
<i>You walked into the party,
like you were walking onto a yacht</i>

1202
01:33:46.320 --> 01:33:49.920
<i>You had your hat pulled down
strategically over one eye</i>

1203
01:33:49.960 --> 01:33:54.520
- You had a scarf, it was apricot
- Strategically tipped below one eye

1204
01:33:54.560 --> 01:33:56.400
<i>...one eye in the mirror</i>

1205
