- As you made sure you had a real cool
- Gavotte

1206
01:33:59.440 --> 01:34:05.080
<i>And all the girls think that they'd be your
partner, they'd be his partner, 'cause</i>

1207
01:34:05.120 --> 01:34:09.760
<i>He's so vain, you probably think
this song is about you</i>

1208
01:34:09.800 --> 01:34:12.880
<i>Ben Barry, you're so vain</i>

1209
01:34:12.920 --> 01:34:17.200
<i>You probably think this song is about
you, don't you, don't you?</i>

1210
01:34:17.240 --> 01:34:19.400
Tone deaf and drunk
is a bad combination.

1211
01:34:19.440 --> 01:34:22.880
You fooled me to win a bet
and you should be ashamed.

1212
01:34:22.920 --> 01:34:27.080
You took me to a Celine Dion concert.
You made me miss the big game.

1213
01:34:27.120 --> 01:34:33.120
Smart guy's a rhymer! Do we want them
to know your love-making is lame?

1214
01:34:33.160 --> 01:34:36.680
Maybe 'cause you named my penis,
yeah, you named my penis,

1215
01:34:36.720 --> 01:34:39.840
you named my penis after a dame!

1216
01:34:39.880 --> 01:34:42.480
You really should get over that.

1217
01:34:42.520 --> 01:34:44.920
- Come on, you're so vain.
- No, you are.

1218
01:34:44.960 --> 01:34:48.720
It's the worst thing I've ever heard.

1219
01:34:48.760 --> 01:34:52.800
<i>'Cause you're so vain!</i>

1220
01:34:54.640 --> 01:34:59.440
You know the words so well, don't you?
There she goes.

1221
01:34:59.480 --> 01:35:01.360
Thanks, guys.

1222
01:35:01.400 --> 01:35:05.360
Take it from here, Marvin.

1223
01:35:05.920 --> 01:35:08.840
Wasn't she wearing
the Isadora diamond?

1224
01:35:08.880 --> 01:35:12.920
Isadora?
Oh, mon Dieu! Security!

1225
01:35:12.960 --> 01:35:17.000
Oh, no, no. Hold on, Andie Anderson,
I'm not done with you.

1226
01:35:17.040 --> 01:35:20.720
You used me to get ahead in your work.

1227
01:35:20.760 --> 01:35:23.200
You arrogant, back-stabbing jerk.

1228
01:35:23.240 --> 01:35:27.400
- Lady, hold it!
- You drove me mad for an article.

1229
01:35:27.440 --> 01:35:31.720
You said you could make any girl
fall in love with you, and I was Exhibit A.

1230
01:35:31.760 --> 01:35:34.240
- Time out.
- What?

1231
01:35:34.280 --> 01:35:41.840
Please, just give me the necklace.
Then you can go on and kill each other.

1232
01:35:43.280 --> 01:35:48.440
That's what I was, huh? I was a guinea
pig. Someone to test your theories on.

1233
01:35:48.480 --> 01:35:52.600
Yeah, and I was just a girl
somebody picked out in a bar.

1234
01:35:52.640 --> 01:35:58.960
Big deal. I'm sure now you can even
use it as a little twist in your story.

1235
01:35:59.000 --> 01:36:02.600
Good idea, maybe we should bet on it.

1236
01:36:02.640 --> 01:36:05.920
Know what? You did your job.

1237
01:36:05.960 --> 01:36:12.560
You wanted to lose a guy in ten days.
Congratulations, you just lost him.

1238
01:36:12.600 --> 01:36:15.680
No, I didn't, Ben.

1239
01:36:15.720 --> 01:36:21.160
'Cause you can't lose
something you never had.

1240
01:36:40.680 --> 01:36:45.160
Well... it's not what I expected.

1241
01:36:47.120 --> 01:36:50.560
It's better. Congratulations.

1242
01:36:50.600 --> 01:36:53.480
This shows me
you're ready to be unleashed.

1243
01:36:53.520 --> 01:36:58.480
From now on,
feel free to write about anything.

1244
01:36:58.520 --> 01:37:03.680
- Anything?
- Wherever the wind blows you.

1245
01:37:04.880 --> 01:37:10.720
- Even politics?
- No, the wind won't blow you there.

1246
01:37:10.760 --> 01:37:14.120
What about religion,
poverty, economics?

1247
01:37:14.160 --> 01:37:18.200
This wind is really more of a light breeze.

1248
01:37:18.240 --> 01:37:22.680
- What can I write about, Lana?
- Whatever you want.

1249
01:37:22.720 --> 01:37:26.440
Shoes, laser therapy,
dressing for your body-type.

1250
01:37:26.480 --> 01:37:31.720
Use your imagination.
The sky is the limit.

1251
01:37:32.800 --> 01:37:37.240
- Thank you for this opportunity.
- OK.

1252
01:37:37.280 --> 01:37:43.240
And thank you for making it
easy for me to turn down.

1253
01:37:46.480 --> 01:37:48.880
It's not something I'm proud of.

1254
01:37:48.920 --> 01:37:56.240
Obviously, if I could do it over again,
I'd do some things differently.

1255
01:37:56.680 --> 01:38:00.480
It's good to talk to you, man. It really is.

1256
01:38:00.520 --> 01:38:06.040
I know. You're the only one
that knows us both.

1257
01:38:13.000 --> 01:38:15.520
You wanna go?

1258
01:38:15.560 --> 01:38:17.960
You wanna go to the game?

1259
01:38:18.000 --> 01:38:20.120
Go ahead, 'cause I'm not going.

1260
01:38:20.160 --> 01:38:23.680
<i>The seventh and final game
of a classic series...</i>

1261
01:38:23.720 --> 01:38:26.200
Sweetie, I wouldn't have gone, either.

1262
01:38:26.240 --> 01:38:32.760
I mean, I'd have liked to,
but you probably wouldn't let me.

1263
01:38:33.360 --> 01:38:37.000
You're doing the right thing.

1264
01:38:37.040 --> 01:38:39.960
Oh, sweetie!

1265
01:38:40.560 --> 01:38:44.080
There's the Chinese.

1266
01:38:44.920 --> 01:38:47.760
I'm coming.

1267
01:38:51.640 --> 01:38:56.560
- OK, so that's gonna be...
- Michelle.

1268
01:38:56.840 --> 01:38:59.880
Andie, that wasn't the Chinese.

1269
01:38:59.920 --> 01:39:02.640
- It's Mike!
- Mike?

1270
01:39:02.680 --> 01:39:06.920
- Yeah, what do I do?
- Talk to him.

1271
01:39:06.960 --> 01:39:10.000
OK, all right.

1272
01:39:11.440 --> 01:39:13.680
OK.

1273
01:39:15.520 --> 01:39:17.880
Mike?

1274
01:39:18.360 --> 01:39:21.320
- Mike!
- Hi.

1275
01:39:21.480 --> 01:39:23.720
Hi.

1276
01:39:24.520 --> 01:39:30.960
- So... what are you doing here?
- I don't know, exactly...

1277
01:39:31.040 --> 01:39:36.680
It was last night.
I was... just lying there, trying to sleep.

1278
01:39:36.720 --> 01:39:41.240
You know that perfume
you sprayed on my pillow?

1279
01:39:41.280 --> 01:39:44.720
- Oh, yeah.
- Well, that smell is gone now.

1280
01:39:44.760 --> 01:39:49.000
And, Michelle, I want it back.

1281
01:39:52.040 --> 01:39:56.800
I don't know if you can have it back.

1282
01:39:58.360 --> 01:40:00.440
Right...

1283
01:40:00.480 --> 01:40:03.160
Yeah. OK.

1284
01:40:04.880 --> 01:40:07.120
But I am...

1285
01:40:07.160 --> 01:40:09.240
...willing to consider it.

1286
01:40:09.280 --> 01:40:11.960
OK. Yeah.

1287
01:40:12.440 --> 01:40:14.920
- These are for you.
- Thank you.

1288
01:40:14.960 --> 01:40:17.200
Hi.

1289
01:40:31.280 --> 01:40:35.240
I remember where you live.

1290
01:40:36.800 --> 01:40:39.840
Who needs men?

1291
01:40:40.320 --> 01:40:44.200
Ladies, frost yourselves.

1292
01:40:50.160 --> 01:40:53.000
And, cut it! Very nice.

1293
01:40:53.040 --> 01:40:55.600
- Superbe.
- OK, let's go one more.

1294
01:40:55.640 --> 01:40:58.440
- Magnifique.
- All right.

1295
01:40:58.480 --> 01:41:00.240
Tim, can I see playback?

1296
01:41:00.280 --> 01:41:05.720
Open me, Ben.
Please break my binding. Please!

1297
01:41:06.680 --> 01:41:09.560
- You might wanna read this.
- No, thanks.

1298
01:41:09.600 --> 01:41:15.840
OK. I've lost a guy and I don't know why.
What went wrong?

1299
01:41:15.880 --> 01:41:20.800
When I started this column, I wanted
to commit those silly dating faux pas.

1300
01:41:20.840 --> 01:41:27.160
What I didn't realise was that I was
making the biggest mistake of all.

1301
01:41:27.200 --> 01:41:29.920
Here. Trust me.

1302
01:41:29.960 --> 01:41:32.560
Read it.

1303
01:41:58.600 --> 01:42:02.560
Excuse me, Andie Anderson?

1304
01:42:11.800 --> 01:42:13.920
- Excuse me, ma'am.
- Holy crap.

1305
01:42:13.960 --> 01:42:16.600
- Where's Andie Anderson?
- She's not here.

1306
01:42:16.640 --> 01:42:19.000
- She quit.
- She has an interview in DC.

1307
01:42:19.040 --> 01:42:20.920
- When's she leaving?
- Today.

1308
01:42:20.960 --> 01:42:24.480
- When?
- Like, now.

1309
01:42:26.160 --> 01:42:30.400
- You're not a therapist, are you?
- Oh... no!

1310
01:42:30.440 --> 01:42:33.720
Good job, though.

1311
01:42:34.280 --> 01:42:37.840
You owe me 300 bucks.

1312
01:44:01.760 --> 01:44:06.840
- Pull over, we need to talk.
- Are you trying to get yourself killed?

1313
01:44:06.880 --> 01:44:13.040
- If that's what it takes. Now, pull over.
- Excuse me, sir. Could you pull over?

1314
01:44:13.080 --> 01:44:16.480
We're on a bridge, lady.
I can't pull over here.

1315
01:44:16.520 --> 01:44:22.880
OK. Do you have an ashtray
or something I can throw up in?

1316
01:44:27.640 --> 01:44:32.160
- What the hell was that?
- Is this true?

1317
01:44:32.200 --> 01:44:34.520
- Ben, please.
- Is this true?

1318
01:44:34.560 --> 01:44:40.920
- Or are you just selling magazines?
- I meant every word.

1319
01:44:44.240 --> 01:44:45.760
Where are you going?

1320
01:44:45.800 --> 01:44:51.760
- I have an interview.
- Yeah, in Washington, I know.

1321
01:44:54.640 --> 01:44:58.125
Where are you going?

1322
01:44:58.160 --> 01:45:02.920
It's the only place
I can write what I wanna write.

1323
01:45:02.960 --> 01:45:08.280
I'm not buying that.
You can write anywhere.

1324
01:45:08.840 --> 01:45:10.880
I think you're running away.

1325
01:45:10.920 --> 01:45:17.560
Save your mind games for your next bet.
I am not running away.

1326
01:45:17.720 --> 01:45:20.400
Bullshit.

1327
01:45:26.360 --> 01:45:29.120
Excuse me?

1328
01:45:30.760 --> 01:45:33.720
You heard me.

1329
01:45:35.240 --> 01:45:37.920
Bullshit.

1330
01:45:39.480 --> 01:45:42.960
Hey, lady. What do you wanna do?

1331
01:45:43.000 --> 01:45:49.960
Take her luggage back to her place,
she has alternate transportation.

1332
01:45:50.000 --> 01:45:53.200
Are you calling my bluff?

1333
01:45:53.240 --> 01:45:56.200
You bet I am.

1334
01:46:12.600 --> 01:46:14.680
Look who came with me.

1335
